  "texts": [
    "Some of these limitations in nanofabrication and misalignments can potentially be addressed by appropriate design and network training strategies that take these factors into account during the deep-learning-based optimization and training of the free-space processor (discussed in Section \"Fabrication complexity and 3D alignment requirements\").",
    "The computational performance of current deep neural networks systems can be understood by the universal approximation theorem 180, which states that multi-layered networks with a sufficient number of hidden units and adequate nonlinear activation functions can approximate any continuous function mapping from closed, bounded space to another one with finite dimensions [180] [181] [182].",
    "To achieve universal function approximation through free-space optical networks, however, materials and neuron designs that can achieve nonlinear optical responses would be needed 73.",
    "Nonlinearity has been implemented in diffractive optical processors using a combination of photodetector/sensor arrays and dynamic electro-optic modulation devices 27, 183.",
    "However, this approach not only significantly increases the complexity of the devices but also introduces undesirable active power consumption to the system."
  ],
